WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.680
In China, many holidays are on the first day of the month.

00:05.680 --> 00:10.520
For example, we celebrate Labor Day on the 1st of May.

00:10.520 --> 00:14.680
Well, we celebrate May Day in the UK.

00:14.680 --> 00:18.040
It's not always on the 1st day of May.

00:18.040 --> 00:21.600
It's on the 1st Monday in May.

00:21.600 --> 00:27.720
In the US, Labor Day is a national holiday, but it's on a different date.

00:27.720 --> 00:31.080
It's on the 1st Monday in September.

00:31.080 --> 00:34.440
It's the last day before the new school year begins.

